<td valign="MIDDLE"><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="000000">Hi, <br>
I have 200 skill in jewelry so I know the road you are on!  I am a 35 level Enchanter on Bertox.  When it says an item is trivial, it means you can no longer advance your skill by making that item...but you CAN still fail when making anything...regardless of your skill level...but the higher it is, the less likely you will be to fail.  At 200, I don't recall failing anything anymore in silver and even very rarely in gold.  But plat NEVER becomes trivial anyway, and you WILL fail alot doing plat.  Good luck!<hr>Joan D'Ark<br>
Enchantress of Bertox<br>
Amazonian Sister Guild</font></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor="DDDDDD">
