<td valign="MIDDLE"><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="000000">message for juyucharm and all the jewelcrafters out there...<br>
i'm an 18 enc with a jewelery skill of about 90. yes, even tho the item may be trivial at your skill level, failures are still common. if you're looking to sell the items you're making, the obvious solution is to make items that sell, and risk failures. or you can hold out on making your money back for a while and work on increasing your skill by buying cheap gems, dont waste time enchanting, and make worthless jewelery until that cheap gem is now trivial. for example: you have a skill of 50ish? you can enchant electrum? buy a whole bunch of (i'm talking 150-200) cheap gems.. cats eye agate, bloodstone and electrum bars. it will take alot of time to increase your skill to the point where thats trivial, but atleast you're not losing out on tons of money using more expensive gems and silver and losing the money all at once. i just sell the items back to the vendor. i've managed to increase my skill by 30 or so points without losing more than 200pp. now i'm ready for the money makers. hope this helps.. good luck<hr>~Khallia</font></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor="DDDDDD">
