<td valign="MIDDLE"><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="000000">I've found it worth the time to enchant the metal first. It doesn't seem to make any difference in the failure rate, and you can sell your success's for a slight profit. But it does take time, and is boring sitting around. TIP Get the highest int. items on you that you have. It cuts the failure rate a lot. Wisdom doesn't help. If there is a 44+ Enchanter in the area, ask them to cast Brilliance (Int buff) on you just before you start. You can pick one item from a stack by hitting Shift(I think) left click. Or something + click, don't really remember which, but it is a real time saver. Good Luck.</font></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor="DDDDDD">
