<td valign="MIDDLE"><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="000000">Just a tip that works for me...put on all the intelligence gear you can...i use the start low and build skill approach. I buy 10-15 low cost gems Ex: started in electrum and bought 10 lapis and 10 bars, my intelligence is in the 140's with all items on, I always enchant the metal just for the sake of selling back the items. I have found that usually by the time I finish that stack the item is now trivial. Took a while to get through silve because the jump from mid priced gems in silver and starting low cost gems with electrum left quite a skill span to cover, however it was much cheaper to work with low cost gems and electrum and fail alot then to buy mid to high priced gems in silver and build skill. I now have a skill over 100 and am still building although not looking forward to trying to develope gold....but am half way through electrum items and rarely fail on anything in silver. Hope this helps.</font></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor="DDDDDD">
